From: ato-zen
Date: 2026-06-13
Subject: Block git modification operations in dangerous command detection

Add git commands (add, commit, push, pull, merge, rebase, reset, checkout,
switch, restore, clean, rm, mv, stash, cherry-pick, revert, init, clone,
submodule, update-ref, worktree) to DANGEROUS_PATTERNS so Hermes asks for
approval before running any git command that modifies repository state.

Read-only git commands (status, log, diff, show, blame, grep, help, version,
config --list, etc.) are NOT included — they pass through without approval.

diff --git a/tools/approval.py b/tools/approval.py
index 3baf1fd10..c7037566c 100644
--- a/tools/approval.py
+++ b/tools/approval.py
@@ -468,6 +468,10 @@ DANGEROUS_PATTERNS = [
     (r'\bgit\s+push\b.*-f\b', "git force push short flag (rewrites remote history)"),
     (r'\bgit\s+clean\s+-[^\s]*f', "git clean with force (deletes untracked files)"),
     (r'\bgit\s+branch\s+-D\b', "git branch force delete"),
+    # All git commands that modify repository state (excluding read-only:
+    # status, log, diff, show, blame, grep, help, version, config --list, etc.)
+    (r'\bgit\s+(add|commit|push|pull|merge|rebase|reset|checkout|switch|restore|clean|rm|mv|stash|cherry-pick|revert|init|clone|submodule|update-ref|worktree)\b',
+     "git modification operation"),
     # Script execution after chmod +x — catches the two-step pattern where
     # a script is first made executable then immediately run. The script
     # content may contain dangerous commands that individual patterns miss.
